Can schools enforce the payment of fees during the lockdown? Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The nationwide lockdown has had a major effect on the economy. President Cyril Ramaphosa has warned that the country will not be spared from job losses. This has made it difficult for some parents to pay school fees. READ: Impact of school closures on education outcomes in South Africa Schools were closed as part of government's measures to curb the spread of the coronavirus. Learning continues online for equipped institutions but parents are questioning if they should be paying school fees in full. READ: SA lockdown: Schools to remain closed in May Legal expert Bulelwa Mabasa from Werksman Attorneys says parents need to negotiate payment with the school. “Even in an independent school, there is a provision that says the best interest of the child must be looked after.” - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.